translated: Falk, Johan Ragnar, county assessor, Vänersborg, born 14/8/90 in Karlstad to factory owner Gustaf F. and Ida Johanson. Married in 1918 to Hildur Ericsson, with one child, Barbro, born in 1919. Graduated from high school in 1909 and received a clerkship degree in 1913. Became an assistant county official in Värmland in January 1915, and a regular official in the same position in Älvsborg in January 1918. Promoted to second-class county accountant in Älvsborg in 1920 and to first-class in 1926. After serving as temporary clerk in the Väne district revenue office in 1927, he became a regular clerk there in 1943 and was appointed Jänsa's assessor at the Älvsborg county board in 1946. He served as auditor in the Vänersborg Savings Bank and the Älvsborg household companionship, as well as cashier in the county council. He was chairman of a special tax committee for the northern part of the county and a representative of the Kingdom of Sweden's City Mortgage Bank in Älvsborg. He was awarded the Order of Vasa (RVO).
